{\b\fs32 SDN Discovery Agent - High-Level Design Document}
\par\par

{\b\fs28 Executive Summary}
\par\par
This document outlines the design for an intelligent agent that automates the creation of SDN vendor implementations from OpenAPI specifications. The agent will analyze existing patterns from 6 implemented SDN vendors and generate complete, production-ready code following established NetMRI SDN architecture patterns.
\par\par

{\b\fs28 Current SDN Implementation Analysis}
\par\par

{\b\fs24 Implemented SDN Vendors}
\par\par

{\b Cisco ACI} - Data Center Fabric
\par {\i Authentication:} Cookie-based session
\par {\i Key Features:} Multi-controller failover, Complex hierarchy (Tenant→BD→EPG)
\par\par

{\b Cisco Meraki} - Cloud-managed networking
\par {\i Authentication:} API Key (X-Cisco-Meraki-API-Key)
\par {\i Key Features:} Organization→Network→Device model, Role-based collection
\par\par

{\b Cisco Viptela} - SD-WAN
\par {\i Authentication:} Cookie-based session
\par {\i Key Features:} Session management, Device-centric data model
\par\par

{\b Juniper Mist} - Cloud-managed Wi-Fi/LAN
\par {\i Authentication:} Bearer Token
\par {\i Key Features:} Org→Site→Device, Edge device support
\par\par

{\b SilverPeak} - SD-WAN
\par {\i Authentication:} API Token (X-Auth-Token)
\par {\i Key Features:} Appliance-centric, CLI command execution
\par\par

{\b\fs24 Architecture Patterns Identified}
\par\par

{\b 1. Three-Layer Architecture}
\par\par
┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐
\par │   SDN_Client    │    │   SDN_Server    │    │  SDN_Plugins    │
\par │   (API Layer)   │───▶│ (Logic Layer)   │───▶│ (Data Layer)    │
\par └─────────────────┘    └─────────────────┘    └─────────────────┘
\par      Perl modules         Business logic       Database schema
\par      HTTP wrappers        Data transformation   Persistence
\par      Authentication       Error handling       Validation
\par\par

{\b 2. Data Collection Categories}
\par • {\b Device Discovery:} Find all manageable devices
\par • {\b System Information:} Basic device details (Model, Serial, Version)
\par • {\b Interface/Port Data:} Physical and logical interfaces
\par • {\b Network Topology:} LLDP/CDP neighbor discovery
\par • {\b Routing Information:} Static/dynamic routes
\par • {\b Wireless Configuration:} SSIDs, radio status (for wireless vendors)
\par • {\b Status/Monitoring:} Operational state, performance metrics
\par\par

{\b 3. Common Data Model}
\par All vendors map to standardized NetMRI fields:
\par\par
\f1\fs20 # Standard device representation
\par \{
\par     SdnControllerId => $fabric_id,
\par     SdnDeviceDN => $unique_device_identifier,
\par     Name => $device_name,
\par     NodeRole => $device_role,
\par     Vendor => $vendor_name,
\par     Model => $device_model,
\par     Serial => $serial_number,
\par     SWVersion => $software_version,
\par     IPAddress => $management_ip,
\par     modTS => $modification_timestamp
\par \}
\f0\fs24
\par\par

{\b 4. Authentication Patterns}
\par • {\b API Key:} Simple header-based (Meraki, SilverPeak, Mist)
\par • {\b Session-based:} Login→Cookie→Operations→Logout (ACI, Viptela)
\par • {\b Token-based:} Bearer tokens with refresh capability
\par\par

{\b 5. Error Handling & Resilience}
\par • Rate limiting (vendor-specific: 3-100 req/sec)
\par • Retry mechanisms for HTTP 429 (Too Many Requests)
\par • Controller failover (ACI multi-controller setup)
\par • Graceful degradation for offline devices
\par\par

{\b\fs28 Agent Architecture Design}
\par\par

{\b\fs24 Core Components}
\par\par

The SDN Discovery Agent consists of several interconnected modules:
\par\par

{\b OpenAPI Parser Engine}
\par • Parse OpenAPI 3.x schemas
\par • Identify authentication schemes
\par • Categorize endpoints by data type
\par • Extract request/response schemas
\par • Detect pagination patterns
\par\par

{\b Pattern Recognition Module}
\par • Map OpenAPI endpoints to NetMRI data collection patterns
\par • Classify endpoints using URL patterns and response indicators
\par • Determine optimal API selection strategies
\par\par

{\b Code Generation Engine}
\par • Generate production-ready Perl modules using templates
\par • Create SDN_Client, SDN_Server, and SDN_Plugin modules
\par • Implement intelligent API selection algorithms
\par • Handle vendor-specific customizations
\par\par

{\b Template System}
\par • Parameterized Perl templates
\par • Variable substitution engine
\par • Conditional logic for vendor differences
\par • Consistent code structure across vendors
\par\par

{\b\fs24 Intelligent API Selection}
\par\par

The agent uses a sophisticated scoring algorithm to select optimal APIs:
\par\par

{\b Priority Scoring Factors:}
\par • Endpoint specificity (device-specific vs. generic)
\par • HTTP method preference (GET for data collection)
\par • Response schema complexity
\par • Vendor-specific best practices
\par\par

{\b Selection Strategy:}
\par • Score all candidate endpoints
\par • Select primary API with highest score
\par • Identify fallback options for resilience
\par • Generate error handling for failed calls
\par\par

{\b\fs24 Data Transformation Engine}
\par\par

Maps vendor-specific API responses to NetMRI data models:
\par\par

{\b Field Mapping Patterns:}
\par • {\b Device Identification:} id, deviceId, serial, uuid, dn → SdnDeviceDN
\par • {\b Management IP:} managementIp, ip, address, mgmtIp, lanIp → IPAddress
\par • {\b Device Role:} device_type + vendor_prefix → NodeRole
\par • {\b Timestamps:} Various formats → standardized NetMRI format
\par\par

